title: SFH on seasonal influenza and hairy crabs (with photos)
content_text:
p>
					Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary 
					for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, after inspecting the 
					Government Vaccination Programme 2016/17 at Ha Kwai Chung 
					General Out-patient Clinic today (November 4): Reporter: As the scheme is being carried out, do you think 
					that it is a good start? Are you worried that there would 
					not be enough jabs and people are not aware that the flu

not be enough jabs and people are not aware that the flu 
					season is coming? Secretary for Food and Health: As we all know, the peak of 
					seasonal influenza will arrive sometime between now and 
					January. In fact, in these few days, the ambient temperature 
					is starting to drop to below 20 degrees Celsius. It is 
					important for us to remind all eligible citizens to take the 
					opportunity of receiving seasonal influenza vaccination 
					either through the Government Vaccination Scheme or the

either through the Government Vaccination Scheme or the 
					Vaccination Subsidy Scheme. The Vaccination Subsidy Scheme 
					has already been started two weeks ago. Up to today, more 
					than 50 000 people have received vaccination. The Chairman 
					of the Hospital Authority has just said that the Government 
					Vaccination Scheme, which only started yesterday, recorded 
					over 10 000 vaccinations.  Reporter: What is the next step the (Food and Environmental

Hygiene) Department will take after meeting the (hairy crab) 
					trade?
